      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "I hear how devastating and isolating it feels when your sense of self seems to vanish completely, leaving you as a hollow shell playing a role you didn't choose. That sensation of unrecognizability in the mirror is a profound form of grief for the person you used to be. Please know that you are not alone in this experience, and even though it feels permanent right now, there are specialists trained to help you rebuild that connection to your own life and identity. You deserve to feel real again, and reaching out to a therapist or counselor can be the first step toward reclaiming that \"you.\"",
